Largecap Stocks Analysis for creating portfolio

Siva Bulusu

14/12/2019

Portfolio creation using blue-chip shares

You are an Equity fund manager focusing in large cap shares, your client has approached you and expressed in interest in building a portfolio of INR 1 Crore, in high-quality blue-chip shares. His criteria for investment is the investment universe is only blue-chip shares (share should be part of Sensex) and he would like to investment only in 5 shares among this universe. With maximum exposure of 30% in a single share.

He has requested you to provide various portfolios with various scenarios.

Analysis

Download top 100 stocks from BSE India website.

Top 100 stocks are downloaded from BSE India website and saved to excel file. The list is by 5-Sep-2019.

The following 10 well known stocks are selected from above list for analysis. Portfolio will be suggested by choosing 5 stocks from this list.

Security Name | Stock Code

TATA CONSULTANCY SERVICES LTD. | TCS

RELIANCE INDUSTRIES LTD. | RELIANCE

HDFC Bank Ltd | HDFCBANK

ITC LTD. | ITC

LARSEN & TOUBRO LTD. | LT

MARUTI SUZUKI INDIA LTD. | MARUTI

ASIAN PAINTS LTD. | ASIANPAINT

ULTRATECH CEMENT LTD. | ULTRACEMCO

STATE BANK OF INDIA | SBIN

COLGATE-PALMOLIVE (INDIA) LTD. | COLPAL

Generate Risk Metrics for selected stocks and analyze

R code has been written to generate VaR, CVaR and Beta values. Data has been pulled from 1-Jan-2000 for analysis by setting the max date. Periodicity is taken as “daily”.

“.BO” is used beside the names of stocks in “getsymbols” function in order to retrieve BSE prices and information. If in case we need NSE information, then “.NS” should be used in the place.

#Create your Portfolio
tickers <- c("COLPAL.BO","ASIANPAINT.BO","HDFCBANK.BO","MARUTI.BO","RELIANCE.BO")
weights <- c(0.30,0.30,0.30,0.05,0.05)
getSymbols(tickers, from=maxDate)
## Warning: COLPAL.BO contains missing values. Some functions will not work if

Port.prices <- na.omit(merge(Ad(COLPAL.BO),Ad(ASIANPAINT.BO),Ad(HDFCBANK.BO),Ad(MARUTI.BO),Ad(RELIANCE.BO)))
Port.returns <- ROC(Port.prices, type = "discrete")[-1,]

#Give column names to your portfolio
colnames(Port.returns) <- tickers

Calculate Portfolio VaR and CVaR of your Portfolio

#Calculate Individual stocks VaR by historical method
VaR.Hist <- VaR(Port.returns, p=0.95, weights = NULL, portfolio_method = "single",method = "historical")

All.VaR <- abs(data.frame(rbind(VaR.Hist)))
rownames(All.VaR) <- c("Hist")

#Calculate Portfolio VaR by by historical method
PortVaR.Hist <- as.data.frame(VaR(Port.returns,p=0.95,weights=weights, portfolio_method = "component", method = "historical"))[1,1]
## Warning in (function (..., row.names = NULL, check.rows = FALSE, check.names =
## TRUE, : row names were found from a short variable and have been discarded
#Combine Individual Stocks and Portfolio VaR
All.VaR$Portfolio <- 0
All.VaR$Portfolio <- c(PortVaR.Hist)
All.VaR$Type <- "Hist" 
#Visualization of VaR calculated for individual stocks and Portfolio
library(reshape2)
library(ggplot2)

plotVaR <- melt(All.VaR, variable.name = "Ticker", value.name = "VaR")
## Using Type as id variables
ggplot(plotVaR,aes(x=Type, y=VaR, fill=Ticker)) + geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge")

stock <- getSymbols.yahoo(ticker, from=maxDate, periodicity = "daily", auto.assign=FALSE)[,4]

#Get Prices (can be monthly or weekly)
portfolioPrices <- NULL
for (Ticker in tickers)
  portfolioPrices <- cbind(portfolioPrices,
                           getSymbols.yahoo(Ticker, from=maxDate, periodicity = "daily", auto.assign=FALSE)[,4])
## Warning: COLPAL.BO contains missing values. Some functions will not work if
## objects contain missing values in the middle of the series. Consider using
## na.omit(), na.approx(), na.fill(), etc to remove or replace them.
## Warning: ASIANPAINT.BO contains missing values. Some functions will not work
## if objects contain missing values in the middle of the series. Consider using
## na.omit(), na.approx(), na.fill(), etc to remove or replace them.
## Warning: HDFCBANK.BO contains missing values. Some functions will not work
## if objects contain missing values in the middle of the series. Consider using
## na.omit(), na.approx(), na.fill(), etc to remove or replace them.
## Warning: MARUTI.BO contains missing values. Some functions will not work if
## objects contain missing values in the middle of the series. Consider using
## na.omit(), na.approx(), na.fill(), etc to remove or replace them.
## Warning: RELIANCE.BO contains missing values. Some functions will not work
## if objects contain missing values in the middle of the series. Consider using
## na.omit(), na.approx(), na.fill(), etc to remove or replace them.
#Delete all dates with no prices
portfolioPrices <- portfolioPrices[apply(portfolioPrices,1,function(x) all(!is.na(x))),]
#Rename Columns
colnames(portfolioPrices) <- tickers

#Calculate Returns for Assets: Daily RoC
portfolioReturns <- na.omit(ROC(portfolioPrices, type="discrete"))

#Calculate Aggregate Returns for Portfolio
port_rets <- Return.portfolio(portfolioReturns, weights = NULL, geometric = TRUE)
names(port_rets) <- "Portfolio"

Calculate CAPM.beta.

CAPM.beta(port_rets, bench_ret, Rf = 0)
## [1] 0.123599
